"Abstract As an open interactive and boundless medium the Internet represents the ideal platform for commercial transactions. It inspires young start-up entrepreneurs as well as established enterprises and is constantly giving rise to new forms of business activity. Apart from group buying or community shopping schemes it is online auctions which are becoming increasingly popular these days. At first sight Internet auctions might seem as nothing else but the transfer of a traditional form of business to the new medium. Yet a closer look will reveal that there exist considerable differences that may well cause legal controversy."
